**classicalRamseyNumber and Relationship:**

The classical Ramsey number R(G) counts vertices: minimum N such that K_N 2-coloring yields monochromatic G.

**Key relationship:**
R_hat(G) <= C(R(G), 2) = edges in K_{R(G)}

**For K_{n,n}:** Classical Ramsey grows doubly exponentially: R(K_{n,n}) ~ 2^{2^n}

This shows size Ramsey numbers are fundamentally different - they capture edge efficiency.
